body.value:
The Open Scholars Project is an informal forum to learn about and discuss developments in open access. This community of practice allows FSU researchers and scholars to share experiences with open publishing, open source code and open data across subject areas. It brings faculty, postdocs and graduate students from across disciplines together to implement open praxis in their research projects. The group will meet monthly each semester.

Topic: Open Monographs (Scholarly Books)

Zoom registration: https://fla.st/LY0LRYON

Find OSP on Social Media:

Discord

Facebook Group
